The First Lady and President send warm wishes to all Americans as they celebrate Christmas. They acknowledge that gatherings may be different this year due to the pandemic, but emphasize that Christmas is an opportunity to celebrate the birth of Jesus Christ and express gratitude for the blessings in their lives and country. They highlight the importance of peace, generosity, and faith during the holiday season, and express love and joy shared with family and friends. The President also thanks military families, first responders, law enforcement officers, and frontline medical professionals for their service and sacrifices. They wish all Americans and friends around the world a merry Christmas and a peaceful and prosperous New Year.